channel.name: Newsmax US
channel.title: War Journal: The Incredible WWII Escape of Major Damon Rocky Gause
channel.desc: U.S. Army Maj. Damon "Rocky" Gause escapes a prison camp on the Bataan Peninsula in 1942, and with serviceman William Lloyd Osborne, treks from the Phillippines to Australia in a leaky fishing boat, reaching freedom after 52 days and 3,200 miles.
